# CC0 1.0 Universal

## Statement of Purpose

The laws of most jurisdictions throughout the world automatically confer exclusive Copyright and related rights upon creators and others (hereinafter, "rights holders") upon original works of authorship and other subject matter. The rights holder can use these rights to prevent others from using, copying, adapting, or distributing the work.

Some jurisdictions have exceptions and limitations to these exclusive rights, such as through fair use or fair dealing, or through specific statutory exceptions where the use of the work is permitted without the permission of the rights holder. In addition, there are some uses of a work that may be permitted without the need to obtain the rights holder's permission because of applicable law.

The CC0 legal tool enables the rights holder to waive these rights to the fullest extent allowed by law and to publicly dedicate the work to the public domain.

